Here's a clean implementation using `CommunityToolkit.Mvvm` (included in MAUI templates):

```csharp
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.ComponentModel;
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.Input;

namespace MyApp.ViewModels;

public partial class ProductDetailViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _name = string.Empty;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private decimal _price;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isAvailable;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isBusy;

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task LoadAsync()
    {
        if (IsBusy) return;

        try
        {
            IsBusy = true;

            // Replace with your actual data service call
            await Task.Delay(500);

            Name = "Widget Pro";
            Price = 29.99m;
            IsAvailable = true;
        }
        finally
        {
            IsBusy = false;
        }
    }
}
```

**How it works:**

- `[ObservableProperty]` — source-generates the public property with `PropertyChanged` notification (e.g., `_name` → `Name`).
- `[RelayCommand]` — generates `LoadCommand` (an `IAsyncRelayCommand`) from `LoadAsync()`, which also disables re-entry while running.
- `ObservableObject` — base class implementing `INotifyPropertyChanged`.

**Binding in XAML:**

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:MyApp.ViewModels">
    <ContentPage.BindingContext>
        <vm:ProductDetailViewModel />
    </ContentPage.BindingContext>

    <VerticalStackLayout Padding="16">
        <Label Text="{Binding Name}" FontSize="24" />
        <Label Text="{Binding Price, StringFormat='{0:C}'}" />
        <Label Text="{Binding IsAvailable, StringFormat='In Stock: {0}'}" />
        <ActivityIndicator IsRunning="{Binding IsBusy}" />
        <Button Text="Load" Command="{Binding LoadCommand}" />
    </VerticalStackLayout>
</ContentPage>
```

> **Tip:** If you can't use the toolkit, implement `INotifyPropertyChanged` manually with a `SetProperty` helper, but the source-generator approach above eliminates all that boilerplate.
